tic.toiimg.com/photo/37259551.cms" data-src="https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/msid-103894054,width-50,height-38,resizemode-4/103894054.jpg"></div><figcaption>Answers to why UNESCO chose Ethiopia&rsquo;s Bale Mountains National Park as a natural heritage site</figcaption></a></figure></li></ul></div><!--/yourread.cms?msid=103968522&curmsid=103968522potime:153--><div class="travel_content"><div class="synopsis"><h3>Synopsis</h3><p class="readmorecmt">Tirthan Valley is shaped by lush green landscapes, dense forests, and crystal-clear rivers and streams. The hills here are covered with pine and oak trees, making it a perfect destination for nature lovers and trekkers. </p><p style="display:none;" class="readlesscmt">Tirthan Valley is shaped by lush green landscapes, dense forests, and crystal-clear rivers and streams. The hills here are covered with pine and oak trees, making it a perfect destination for nature lovers and trekkers. <a class="readlesscmt" href="javascript://">Read less</a></p></div><div class="share1"><div class="pssharebox" data-gasent="true"><ul><li class="wbbox"><a onclick="whatsappShare()" href="javascript://" aria-label="WhatsApp" data-ga="Share,atfshare_whatsapp,click"></a></li><li class="fbbox"><a href="#" data-plugin="facebook-share" aria-label="Facebook" data-ga="Share,atfshare_facebook,click"></a></li><li class="twtbox"><a data-plugin="twitter-share" href="#" aria-label="Twitter" data-ga="Share,atfshare_twitter,click"></a></li><li class="linkdinbox"><a data-plugin="linkedin-share" href="#" aria-label="Linkedin" data-ga="Share,atfshare_linkedin,click"></a></li><li class="emailbox email sendarticle"><a href="javascript://" aria-label="Email" data-ga="Share,atfshare_email,click"></a></li></ul></div></div><div class="slideshow"><div itemprop="articleBody" class="description box1"><div><div><div data-image="TopLeadImage" class="alC"><span style="position:relative;z-index:0" itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject" itemscope="itemscope" itemprop="image"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/103968581/Tirthan.jpg?width=1200&amp;height=900"><meta itemprop="width" content="1200"><meta itemprop="height" content="900"><img class="lazy" alt="Tirthan Valley: Discovering the secrets of Himachal's hidden beauty" title="Tirthan Valley: Discovering the secrets of Himachal's hidden beauty" src="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/37259551.cms" data-src="https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/103968581/Tirthan.jpg?width=636&amp;height=358&amp;resize=4" onerror="this.src='https://static.toiimg.com/photo/36381469.cms'"><span class="ImageCredit" id="103968581"></span><p style="background: black;color: white;text-align: center;"></p></span></div>Tirthan Valley is a beautiful region in the Kullu district of Himachal Pradesh. This valley is named after the Tirthan River, which flows through it and is a tributary of the Beas River. The valley is known for its stunning natural beauty, serene environment, and rich biodiversity.<br><br><a target="_blank" rel="" href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/travel/destinations/these-himachal-destinations-are-a-winter-wonderland/photostory/97045422.cms"><strong class="">Read more: These Himachal Destinations Are A Winter Wonderland!</strong></a> <div class="first_mrec_ads_photostory"><div class="mh_250 mweb" data-value="MREC_300_MOB" data-plugin="dynad-mob" id="div-gpt-ad-1576740235716-3-103968522"></div></div><div xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns:java="java" xmlns:dateUtil="com.indiatimes.cms.utilities.CMSDateUtility" class="popular_in_sec"><h2 class="amphdng">More from Travel News</h2><div class="remaning_news"><ul><li><a href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/travel/travel-news/holi-special-trains-announced-for-smooth-travel-to-popular-destination/articleshow/118742081.cms" data-ga="MoreFromTravelNews,MoreFromTravelNews_1_https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/travel/travel-news/holi-special-trains-announced-for-smooth-travel-to-popular-destination/articleshow/118742081.cms,click"><span><span><img class="dummy-img list_thumb" src="https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/height-66,width-80,msid-118742081/118742081.jpg" data-hero="" width="80" height="66" tabindex="0" layout="responsive" alt="Holi special trains announced for smooth travel to popular destination"></span>Holi special trains announced for smooth travel to popular destination<span class="time-stamp"></span></span></a></li><li><a href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/travel/travel-news/donald-trump-announces-gold-card-us-visa-what-it-means-especially-for-indians/articleshow/118572287.cms" data-ga="MoreFromTravelNews,MoreFromTravelNews_2_https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/travel/travel-news/donald-trump-announces-gold-card-us-visa-what-it-means-especially-for-indians/articleshow/118572287.cms,click"><span><span><img class="dummy-img list_thumb" src="https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/height-66,width-80,msid-118572287/118572287.jpg" data-hero="" width="80" height="66" tabindex="0" layout="responsive" alt="Donald Trump announces &lsquo;Gold Card&rsquo; US Visa: What it means, especially for Indians"></span>Donald Trump announces &lsquo;Gold Card&rsquo; US Visa: What it means, especially for Indians<span class="time-stamp"></span></span></a></li><li><a href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/travel/travel-news/mumbai-flower-festival-2025-a-blossoming-tribute-to-indias-cultural-heritage/articleshow/117894356.cms" data-ga="MoreFromTravelNews,MoreFromTravelNews_3_https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/travel/travel-news/mumbai-flower-festival-2025-a-blossoming-tribute-to-indias-cultural-heritage/articleshow/117894356.cms,click"><span><span><img class="dummy-img list_thumb" src="https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/height-66,width-80,msid-117894356/117894356.jpg" data-hero="" width="80" height="66" tabindex="0" layout="responsive" alt="Mumbai Flower Festival 2025: A colourful tribute to India&rsquo;s cultural heritage"></span>Mumbai Flower Festival 2025: A colourful tribute to India&rsquo;s cultural heritage<span class="time-stamp"></span></span></a></li></ul></div><span class="load-more"><a class="moreBtn trackMoreButtonGA mnewsbtn" data-ga="MoreFromTravelNews,MoreFromTravelNews_click,click" href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/travel/travel-news">More  News</a></span></div><!--/common_widget.cms?v=2&excludemsid=103968522&msid=76255752&tag=articlelistroot&perpage=4&secnameval=Travel News&reqfrm=popular&morelink=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/travel/travel-newspotime:60--><br><!-- could not get data --> <!--/travel/travel_dubai_ads_widget.cms?adonpage=2potime:2-->Here are some unique features and attractions of Tirthan Valley:<br><br><em>Nature’s beauty</em>: Tirthan Valley is shaped by lush green landscapes, dense forests, and crystal-clear rivers and streams. The hills here are covered with pine and oak trees, making it a perfect destination for nature lovers and trekkers.<div class="taboola_ad_mid mweb"><div data-pagetype="article" data-placement="Mid Article Thumbnails 1" data-mode="thumbnails-mid-mobile" data-target_type="mix" class="wdt-taboola" id="taboola-mid-article-thumbnails-103968522"></div></div><br><em>Great Himalayan National Park</em>: The Great Himalayan National Park, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, is one of the major attractions of Tirthan Valley. The park is home to a wide variety of flora and fauna, including several endangered species like the Western Tragopan and snow leopard. <br><br><div class="banner_local mobile_ctn MREC2 mrg10"></div><em>Trekking</em>: Tirthan Valley offers numerous trekking trails, ranging from easy to challenging. Popular treks include the Tirthan Valley Trek, the Jalori Pass Trek, and the Serolsar Lake Trek. Visitors can also enjoy camping, fishing, and river crossing here.<br><br><em>      <div data-image="TopLeadImage" class="alC"><span style="position:relative;z-index:0"><img class="lazy" alt="Tirthan Valley: Discovering the secrets of Himachal's hidden beauty" title="Tirthan Valley: Discovering the secrets of Himachal's hidden beauty" src="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/37259551.cms" data-src="https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/103968585/Great-Himalayan-National-Park1.jpg?width=636&amp;height=358&amp;resize=4" onerror="this.src='https://static.toiimg.com/photo/36381469.cms'"><span class="ImageCredit" id="103968585"></span><p style="background: black;color: white;text-align: center;"></p></span></div>Serolsar Lake</em>: Set close to the Jalori Pass, Serolsar Lake is a serene alpine lake surrounded by thick forests. It's a popular trekking destination and offers a tranquil escape from the hustle and bustle of city life.<br><br><em>Villages</em>: The hamlets in Tirthan Valley are inhabited by indigenous communities like the Gaddis and the Kullus. Visitors can experience the local culture and interact with the villagers and learn about their customs and traditions.<br><br><a target="_blank" rel="" href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/travel/web-stories/a-quick-guide-on-how-to-spend-7-days-in-himachal-pradesh/photostory/98468656.cms"><strong class="">Read more: A quick guide on how to spend 7 days in Himachal Pradesh<br></strong></a><br><em>Trout fishing</em>: The Tirthan River is noted for its trout fishing. Anglers from all over the world visit the valley to try their luck at catching brown and rainbow trout. Permits for fishing in the area are required.<br><em><br>      <div data-image="TopLeadImage" class="alC"><span style="position:relative;z-index:0"><img class="lazy" alt="Tirthan Valley: Discovering the secrets of Himachal's hidden beauty" title="Tirthan Valley: Discovering the secrets of Himachal's hidden beauty" src="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/37259551.cms" data-src="https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/103968592/Great-Himalayan-National-Park.jpg?width=636&amp;height=358&amp;resize=4" onerror="this.src='https://static.toiimg.com/photo/36381469.cms'"><span class="ImageCredit" id="103968592"></span><p style="background: black;color: white;text-align: center;"></p></span></div>A soulful abode</em>: Tirthan Valley is a great place to unwind and disconnect from the chaos of modern life. The tranquil surroundings and the soothing sound of the river make it an ideal destination for those seeking peace and relaxation.<br><br>Tirthan Valley is best visited during the summer and autumn months when the weather is pleasant and the landscapes are at their most vibrant.<br></div></div><script type="text/javascript">
